StorytellingData.Title: Rundown 005
StorytellingData.SurfaceDescription:
Rundown Protocol 4.5 completed. Access from section R4E1 established. Overarching objective to <color=red>probe deeper</color> remains.

Booster reward protocol in effect: Prisoners that retrieve crystal encased <color=red>artifacts</color> from around the structure will be rewarded with <color=red>Attribute Booster Modules</color>, increasing their chances of survival.

Findings from locations with high <color=red>Artifact heat</color> will be rewarded more generously.

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Floodways in lockdown, override required to allow further reconnaissance.
Unknown ceiling dwelling biomass present. Prisoners failing to exercise caution will not be considered a loss.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>...
>...[whispering] Crouch, move slowly, don't shine on them with your flashlight...
<size=200%><color=red>>...[whispering] It's pulsating - don't move!</color></size>

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Prisoners sent to locate and retrieve hisec crate.
Unknown ceiling dwelling biomass present. Prisoners failing to exercise caution will not be considered a loss.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>...Wasn't this room empty before?
<size=200%><color=red>>...I told you those black cocoons were bad news...</color></size>
>...Fuck, I hate this place even more now.

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Specific DNA sample needed. Prisoners sent to retrieve HSU with matching tissue quality.
Air filtration system unstable. Prisoners deemed expendable.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>...Those horned monsters... they're- they're everywhere.
<size=200%><color=red>>...Hit them in the back, even better if they're sleeping.</color></size>
>...[sudden noise]
>...Too late now! Aaargh!
>...[commotion, unintelligible]

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription: Retrieve specific chemical compounds at any cost of prisoners.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
<size=200%><color=red>>...Spitters.</color></size>
>...[long pause]
>...[whispering]I hate spitters.
>...[sudden blast, commotion]

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
The previously acquired hisec crate requires processing.
Prisoners sent to locate and operate machinery needed for further treatment of the crate.
Roaming hostile creatures present. Low prisoner survival rate expected.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>...They just keep coming!
<size=200%><color=red>>...Focus on the objective! Our best chance of survival is pushing forward!</color></size>

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Network link required to obtain control over floodways quadrant maintenance systems.
Prisoners sent to establish terminal uplink.
Low prisoner survival rate expected.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>...Shit, we barely survived that, my ammo is-
>...[whispering] Schh! Door's opening!
>...[gasp]
<size=200%><color=red>>...What the absolute fuck...</color></size>

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Essential quadrant systems offline.
Prisoners sent to bring back power at any cost, in order to facilitate further exploration.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>...What's that, in the darkness?!
<size=200%><color=red>>...The- the darkness... it's moving!</color></size>
>...[screaming, commotion]

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Quadrant reactor needs to be shut down so that security systems go offline and grant access to deeper parts of the structure.
Very low prisoner survival rate expected.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>...We're shutting every life preserving system down. Survival here is getting harder by the minute.
>...It's like Warden knows we're not coming back to this sublevel ever again...
<size=200%><color=red>>...They're gonna send us even deeper.</color></size>

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Security clearance for section B needed. DNA sample will suffice.
Prisoners sent to locate Administrator in stasis unit.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>...
<size=200%><color=red>>..they react to light and sounds!</color></size>
>..stand still! [unintelligible, scream]

Officer Personal ID needed to access powergrid.
Prisoners will be sent down to gather any and all PID.

>..Ssssh [unintelligible]
<size=200%><color=red>>Don't move when their hearts beat!</color></size>
>..Careful, quiet! [scream, gunfire, unintelligible].

Storage subcomplex

Prisoners spent to gain access by powergrid shutdown.
High death rate estimated.

>[unintelligible]

<size=200%><color=red>>...everyone is dead</color></size>
>..I can't....I won't make it
>[gunfire]

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription: Prisoners sent to get a generator cluster back online for the centralized air purification system of the Reactor.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>..the air is so.. thick.. [coughing]
<size=200%><color=red>>..hurry, let's get these generators back online!</color></size>
>..it should make it easier to breathe..

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription: Power out in section B1. Reactor to be brought online at any cost of prisoners.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>..They keep coming..!
<size=200%><color=red>>..keep firing..! </color></size>
>..wait..what the hell is this?! ..spread out and search!
Descriptive.DevInfo:
Short reactor level
Combat with timed excursions
Abundant ammo

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription: Protocols needed for neural imprinting. Prisoners sent to find uplink and retrieve.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>..Wait.. What could The Warden possibly do with this..?
<size=200%><color=red>>..do you really want to know..?</color></size>

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
HydroStasis Depressurizer(DPR) needed to access resuscitated NeonateHSU contents.
Prisoners used to find a DPR unit and depressurise the NeonateHSU.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>..are we really putting it in that.. thing..?
>..just shut up and get on with it already! 
<size=200%><color=red>>We've got ..INCOMING!!</color></size>
 [gunfire]
Descriptive.DevInfo: Straight mainpath with lateral optional zones

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
DNA sample retrieved during ALPHA protocol corrupted.
Needed for Neural Imprint.
Prisoners spent on retrieval.
<color=red>--ERR : ROT47 --
&?6IA64E65 86@8C2A9:42= 52E2 >:D>2E49[ 2C62 566>65 F?DE23=6]</color>
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>..its ..changed...
<size=150%><color=red>>..shut up and keep your eyes open!</color></size>
>..[unintelligible]

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Imprinted Neonate needs to be secured and connected to the Neural Frame (nFrame).
Prisoners <color=red>::ERR ###</color>
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>..We shouldn't do this... it feels wrong..
<size=200%><color=red>>..We.. have no choice</color></size>
>..wait.. what the hell is that sound?!
>...[distant roar]
Descriptive.DevInfo:
Starts with trickle - deactivates at HSU station
Last part of level - pure sneak and Boss

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Rundown Protocol 3.0 completed. Access from section R3D1 established.
Comprehensive research data required for further development.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>...
>...What's behind this big bulkhead door?
>...Better leave it alone.
<size=200%><color=red>>...yeah, you got a death wish?</color></size>

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Cryo cases in power conservation mode expected to still contain useful resources.
Prisoners sent to locate and extract two articles.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>.."Threat level overload"..
>..I don't like the sound of that.
<size=150%><color=red>>..If we gotta go there, let's save it for last.</color></size>
Descriptive.DevInfo: Retrieve + HSU +Terminal command (Evil exit wave)

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription: Maintenance work required in the eastern quadrant. Clear a path. Low prisoner survival rate expected.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
<size=200%><color=red>>...We're running out of resources...</color></size>
>...At least we have the foam grenades, might as well put them to good use.

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Extensive power is needed for further progress.
Connect as many power cells as possible to the local power grid, routing power to the [Z085] power cluster.
Prisoners deemed expendable.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>..These things are fucking heavy.
<size=200%><color=red>>..[whispering]Schh! You'll wake up the big ones.</color></size>
>..[whispering] Yeah shut up and carry on.
Descriptive.DevInfo:
Layer 1: Distribute 3 power cells
Layer 2: Reactor startup, 5 waves

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Unexpected fog conditions in [Z085].
Stabilize climate control system at any cost of prisoners.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>..Can't see shit through this fucking fog.. [coughing]
<size=200%><color=red>>..let's just get that generator cluster running!</color></size>
>..Yeah it might just help. It might..

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription: Access to the eastern quadrant established. Locate three separate network nodes and set up the local network.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>...This bioscan--
<size=200%><color=red>>...GET BACK IN! It's going backwards!</color></size>
>...Oh fuck!

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Explicit nFrame units exceeding capacity.
Allocate Data Spheres to prisoner groups to salvage nFrame data.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>..What the fuck is that?!
>..Holy SHIT!
<size=200%><color=red>>..SHOOT THE TUMORS ON THE BACK!</color></size>

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Specific congeners required for next phase.
Prisoners sent to amass articles of interest.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>..No, not that thing- not again!
<size=200%><color=red>>..INCOMING!!</color></size>
[gunfire, commotion]

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription: Locate and extract FRT (Fog Repeller Turbine) before this part of the facility is closed off. Do not damage the equipment.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>...How do we get past?
<size=200%><color=red>>...We need fog repellers. Lots of 'em.</color></size>

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
The quadrant's main power source ready to be brought back online.
Prisoners sent to execute startup sequence.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
[gunfire, commotion]
>..Hey! See that, uh.. evil looking stuff in the ceiling?
>..Yeah, what is that?
<size=150%><color=red>>..I think I've seen this before..</color></size>

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription:
Unknown hostile lifeform readings in subjacent quadrant.
Expendable prisoners sent to survey threat severity.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
>..wait.. what the hell is that sound?!
<size=200%><color=red>>..aw FUCK!</color></size>
>..CIRCLE AROUND IT!
[gunfire, screams]

Descriptive.ExpeditionDescription: Locate and install displaced power cells. Beware of unidentified motile biomass.
Descriptive.RoleplayedWardenIntel:
<size=200%><color=red>>...The fog... is it-- uh, moving?</color></size>
>...Yeah I was just about to say.
>...This place is getting more and more claustrophobic by the minute.
